	(text "Programming Note:-\n\nIf you are re-programming the UPduino in situ via the J1 micro USB connector\nuse a USB cable/adapter where the +5 V (VBUS) conductor is disconnected, \nbut D+, D− & GND remain.\n\nPowering the UPduino from the SmartSwitch's 5 V will ensure no +5v contention\nwith the USB's own 5v supply. \n\nIf a regular USB cable is used Diode D5 will provide protection to the SmartSwitch's +5v\nbut it will not protect the PC's USB port."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 127.254 35.052 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "Verdana")
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(italic yes)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "77485e6c-2c71-405c-830c-4066d87ca481")
	)
